We munched on healthy snacks and worked hard until we got scared off by the sprinklers. ü§™üí¶ If you are interested in helping out with the garden, it will need love all summer, so reach out to Coach D. We are excited to harvest the fruits of our labors this fall!
text: We are GROWING GREENWOOD one student and one plant at a time in our school garden! Thank you to all our amazing family volunteers who showed up to our little garden party on Tuesday. We munched on healthy snacks and worked hard until we got scared off by the sprinklers. ü§™üí¶ If you are interested in helping out with the garden, it will need love all summer, so reach out to Coach D. We are excited to harvest the fruits of our labors this fall!

post_text: We are excited to have Mrs. Deena Blanch returning next school year! She is very kind and loving to all GW students, and is willing to jump in and help where needed.

Join Coach D in 30 mins for the first in her series on Mindfulness. We encourage parents to join their children and practice along with them!

These are uncertain times and mindfulness practice can give us a respite from the chaos!

Join us! Facebook live, Instagram live and if you miss it, we will post the video here to watch later!

Do this for you as parent and now homeschool teacher, do it for your children, do it for the collective good of our planet!

See you at 9:00am!

Letter from the Director 3/20/3020
Join us in celebrating ‚ÄúSpirit Week‚Äù with the entire state! I thought it might be fun to connect over social media or to have the kids send fun pictures in to their teachers of them participating. We need to bring a little fun back and we miss their cute faces! :)

I also wanted to remind you to make sure you pick up your breakfast/lunches each day. If you can get to the school by 9:00 a.m. that would be great. If not, contact the office. The office can hold them for you, but they will only be there until 12:00 p.m. If you did not order lunches but need to, please contact the office Monday morning or email info@greenwoodcharter.org.

Have a great weekend!

Mrs. Nelsen

We know our choices have consequences. We conduct every interaction honestly. We set intention. We commit to act. We reflect on growth and the impact of our decisions. post_text:
Oh @sharewinterfoundation, do you know what you have done??!!

Along with @powdermountain you all have made some dreams come true and futures a little sweeter!

You've given kids who would have never gotten an experience like this and made it possible!

There has been challenging moments, acts of true grit, use of growth mindset, friendships made, mindful moments with parents and lots of falling down and getting back up!

These students have been bruised and battered but we guarantee with all the sore bodies and runny noses, this has been the time of their lives and one they will never forget! #sharewinterfoundation #sharewinter #howdoyougw #powmowkids #powmow #luckyslice #shredbetties #winter #kidssnowboarding #healthyhabits @protectourwinters @shredbetties @eleducation #getonthebus #pizza #skiing #buddysystem #nevercalllastrun #lovetheseshredders @ Powder Mountain

post_text:
We had the BEST time during our "Winter Sports Intensives"

‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢

As an @eleducation school we provide opportunities that teach growth mindset, adventure, facing fear, working as a team, healthy habits and so much more!

For our Winter Sports Intensive 6th, 7th and 8 graders got to take ski and snowboard lessons @powdermountain for 3 days. For their service day they filmed a professional video for @powdermountain, a "how to" for other schools. The students were very professional and did a great job! After that the students went to the @utaholympicoval and learned how to do the sport of Curling. @utaholympicovalcurling
They learned from Olympic medalist Derek Parra.

We had such an amazing time, one I don't think these students will ever forget. #howdoyougw #healthyhabits #skiing #snowboarding #winter #wintersports #mindfulness

post_text: You're invited! Our Early Grove teachers have been hard at work planning an amazing intensive for kindergarten through second grade! Students will wonder about the scientific forces at work as they play together during their initial visit to active play hot spot Fly High in Ogden this Friday! Then, they will become scientists as they research the forces of motion affecting these activities. Finally, they will work in mixed-age groups to present what they've learned at our exhibition night at Fly High on Thursday, Dec. 19th at 5:00 pm! You're invited to come hear our kids teach you what they've learned and experience the forces of motion side by side with the kids for yourselves! All of our GreenWood families are welcome to come! More details to come in Mrs. Nelsen's Sunday email!

post_text:
October's H.E.A.L.T.H. Value is Achievement <3
Discuss with your students what achievement means to them. We just had Learner Goal Conferences. Make sure you follow up to see how they are doing!

We know that to succeed, we need to know how we fail. Knowing ourselves first, we focus on growth with an open mindset. My ability and competence grow with my effort. We ask questions that solve authentic problems. We strive to surpass yesterday's accomplishments, and prepare diligently to excel in every arena. We have the confidence to compete when success is not assured. We persevere in the face of challenge, and view every failure as the basis for a future success. We objectively analyze past experiences to improve our knowledge. We are passionate about excellence. We have grit.

Letter from the Director, 9/30/19

Parent Suns,

Thank you for coming to participate in Learner Goal Conferences! We had an amazing turn out and it was fantastic to see all of you involved with your students. If you were unable to attend please make arrangements with your child‚Äôs teacher to come in and set goals with your student. It was so powerful to see you in crew and then working with your students to set goals for their future! We have seen so much growth in our students this year both academically and in their character. We can‚Äôt wait to see the progress they make for their Student Led Conferences in November.

Let's have another great week at Greenwood! We only have 2 weeks before Fall Break comes and the quarter ends! We are already approaching the ¬º mark! Together we are ROCKING it this year! Please let us know if you have questions or concerns. We are so grateful for all of you!

~ Mrs. Nelsen

post_text:
Letter from the Director 9/9/19

Parent Suns,

Last Wednesday was our first Forest Crew (thanks Coach D!) and it went really well! We learned about the Trash Vortex and how to take care of our environment. You may want to ask your student how they are helping to take care of Greenwood. We committed to pick up trash and our equipment on the playground this month. We also touched a little on how being kind and the way that we speak are part of being an environmental steward. We had our first camp out of the year with Upper Grove! It was so fun to spend time with them outdoors. Thanks to our fabulous Upper Grove teachers and Dubois for planning and carrying out a really great outdoor experience for our students. This week we will finish up our beginning of the year testing and get fully into our targeted instruction time. I can‚Äôt wait to see how our kids excel this year!

I‚Äôm looking forward to another amazing week at Greenwood! We have awesome families and we are really ROCKING GREENWOOD this year! :)

Mrs. Nelsen

post_text:
Letter from the Director 9/2/2019

Hello Parent Suns!

I hope that all of you had a fabulous Labor Day weekend and had some time to spend outdoors with your family! It was really nice for me to get reconnected with nature this weekend with mine, especially since we are focusing on Environmental Stewardship this month.

We had a very successful Family Crew meeting last Wednesday. Thank you to all of you who came and who were so willing to volunteer!

We also had some great fieldwork last week. We really have amazing parents and we want to say THANK YOU to all of you that have been doing so much to make GreenWood awesome this year.

We have our Middle School Opening Camp Out this week. I can‚Äôt wait to spend some time outdoors with them!

As always if you have questions or concerns, let us know! Thanks for being amazing. Let‚Äôs have a fabulous week.

Mrs. Nelsen

Clark and Grose/Drake's crew went on their first expedition of the school year! It was amazing to canoe on Causey Lake! 4th and 5th graders took time to discuss the terrain, talk proper paddling techniques, team work and mindfulness out in nature.
